Correlation between variable
Pearson correlation,

corre coeffeicent,
p-value

correlation coeef
-+1 large positive
-1 large negative.

p-value  < 0.001 very good.

example.
pearson_coef, p_value = stats.pearsonr(df['horsepower'],df['price'])

